The [[US State|State]] of [[Wyoming]] first required its residents to register their [[motor vehicles]] and display [[license plates]] in [[1913]]. License plates are issued and regulated by the [[Wyoming Department of Transportation]] through its Motor Vehicle Services division. Wyoming license plates have included an image of a [[Bucking Horse and Rider]] since 1936, constituting the longest-running license plate motif in the world.
